WEBVTT

1
00:01:14.839 --> 00:01:19.339
BASED ON A TRUE STORY

2
00:02:49.479 --> 00:02:51.279
Birger Eriksen.

3
00:03:39.439 --> 00:03:40.679
Right ...

4
00:03:40.759 --> 00:03:45.259
We just saw photos from
the sinking of the German cruiser Blücher.

5
00:03:45.919 --> 00:03:49.959
One of the most talked about
events of the war in Norway.

6
00:03:49.999 --> 00:03:54.499
It was sunk by Oscarsborg Fortress
under the command of Colonel Eriksen.

7
00:03:55.119 --> 00:03:57.599
who has joined us today.

8
00:03:58.599 --> 00:04:01.959
May I ask why I've been
summoned by this Commission?

9
00:04:04.239 --> 00:04:08.639
Our task is to investigate
military matters from 1940.

10
00:04:09.239 --> 00:04:12.159
I've written
a number of reports on the issue.

11
00:04:12.239 --> 00:04:14.759
Which we have read.

12
00:04:16.439 --> 00:04:20.159
But we need more information
for the official report.

13
00:04:20.999 --> 00:04:25.499
We register that there are
conflicting reports from this event.

14
00:04:25.959 --> 00:04:30.459
-You don't believe my reports?
-We don't <i>believe</i> anything. Eriksen.

15
00:04:34.599 --> 00:04:39.099
Maybe you can start by describing
the situation at Oscarsborg and the events

16
00:04:41.039 --> 00:04:44.039
that took place there April six years ago?

17
00:05:06.479 --> 00:05:10.979
<i>As reported by the BBC
in a statement broadcast at 8 a.m..</i>

18
00:05:12.119 --> 00:05:16.619
<i>British and French warships deployed
mines in Norwegian waters last night.</i>

19
00:05:18.079 --> 00:05:22.579
<i>The Foreign Secretary expounded
on the French-British minelaying activity.</i>

20
00:05:23.039 --> 00:05:27.279
SERIOUS VIOLATIONS OF
NORWEGIAN NEUTRALITY

21
00:05:30.479 --> 00:05:32.679
Commander's office. Oscarsborg.

22
00:05:33.719 --> 00:05:35.479
Yes. one moment.

23
00:05:36.199 --> 00:05:37.759
Father.

24
00:05:37.839 --> 00:05:40.919
It's Horten naval command. Smith-Johannsen.

25
00:05:44.839 --> 00:05:47.799
-This is Eriksen.
<i>-Good day. Colonel.</i>

26
00:05:47.879 --> 00:05:49.719
<i>This is Admiral Smith-Johannsen.</i>

27
00:05:49.799 --> 00:05:54.299
<i>We have multiple reports of
German and British ships in our waters.</i>

28
00:05:56.959 --> 00:06:01.459
<i>I have decided to keep the alert level at
"heightened vigilance" until further notice.</i>

29
00:06:02.639 --> 00:06:04.999
<i>Nothing further to report.</i>

30
00:06:05.079 --> 00:06:07.439
Are we going to lay mines?

31
00:06:07.599 --> 00:06:10.119
<i>No. not for you. not that far up the fjord.</i>

32
00:06:10.199 --> 00:06:13.119
<i>We might do it further out in the Oslofjord.</i>

33
00:06:13.199 --> 00:06:17.679
<i>But there's no need to take any measures
at the reserve fortresses.</i>

34
00:06:17.759 --> 00:06:19.279
I see ...

35
00:06:19.359 --> 00:06:21.239
Roger that. Thank you.

36
00:06:29.919 --> 00:06:31.599
Any news?

37
00:06:31.679 --> 00:06:34.999
We maintain current alert levels.

38
00:06:37.719 --> 00:06:40.119
Can you sign this while I've got you here?

39
00:06:41.959 --> 00:06:43.479
Father?

40
00:06:43.639 --> 00:06:46.799
You need to sign this. so I can return it.

41
00:06:49.399 --> 00:06:51.279
And this arrived.

42
00:07:05.279 --> 00:07:06.839
Another rejection?

43
00:07:07.319 --> 00:07:09.879
They'll never agree to any upgrades.

44
00:07:09.959 --> 00:07:12.039
We'll just keep applying.

45
00:07:13.639 --> 00:07:16.839
How many years will
that take. do you think?

46
00:07:16.919 --> 00:07:19.479
You will be retired by then. anyway.

47
00:07:21.479 --> 00:07:23.919
A thing long overdue.

48
00:07:23.959 --> 00:07:25.959
Are you calling your father old?

49
00:07:28.679 --> 00:07:30.039
Yes.

50
00:07:32.359 --> 00:07:34.399
I do.

51
00:07:34.479 --> 00:07:36.159
And out of shape.

52
00:07:39.399 --> 00:07:43.899
I just look forward to
when you're done with all this.

53
00:08:23.079 --> 00:08:26.759
-Any news?
-No. Alert level maintained.

54
00:08:26.839 --> 00:08:30.479
-Did you fix the issue?
-Yes. It was the lock on cannon 3.

55
00:08:30.639 --> 00:08:33.759
You were right. Almost rusted through.

56
00:08:33.839 --> 00:08:36.959
We've spent all day
getting it to move smoothly.

57
00:08:36.999 --> 00:08:39.719
Good. Keep slathering it on. Bonsak.

58
00:08:39.799 --> 00:08:43.759
I told Sødem here that we need
a shit ton of lubricating oil.

59
00:08:43.839 --> 00:08:47.959
But I very much doubt this
Labour government will spare the funds.

60
00:08:55.279 --> 00:08:59.639
-Is the Drøbak searchlight operational?
-So I've been told.

61
00:08:59.719 --> 00:09:01.639
So you've "been told"?

62
00:09:01.719 --> 00:09:05.959
In the week I've been here.
I haven't got around to everything yet.

63
00:09:06.039 --> 00:09:10.539
But I'll go in person tonight to verify.

64
00:09:21.439 --> 00:09:25.939
DRØBAK. MAINLAND

65
00:09:28.479 --> 00:09:31.239
What are your plans going forward?

66
00:09:31.319 --> 00:09:33.479
Once you retire. I mean.

67
00:09:34.119 --> 00:09:35.959
Are you moving up north?

68
00:09:38.199 --> 00:09:42.679
-I didn't mean to intrude.
-We're moving down south.

69
00:09:42.759 --> 00:09:44.959
Oh yes?

70
00:09:44.999 --> 00:09:47.959
-Here. to Drøbak.
-You don't say?

71
00:09:48.039 --> 00:09:51.399
-We've found a house in Seimbakken.
-I see.

72
00:09:51.479 --> 00:09:55.599
Drøbak is a fine place to live.
We've got a great bakery.

73
00:09:55.679 --> 00:09:59.319
I doubt you will run into me at the bakery.

74
00:10:00.479 --> 00:10:03.919
Lucie has made food.
There's enough for one more.

75
00:10:05.239 --> 00:10:07.959
Thank you. but I need to get going.

76
00:10:13.919 --> 00:10:15.919
KOPÅS，MAINLAND
How many men do you have?

77
00:10:15.959 --> 00:10:19.239
Two of the boys were sent home with a cold.

78
00:10:19.319 --> 00:10:21.479
So presently. we're twenty-seven.

79
00:10:23.479 --> 00:10:27.599
Weren't we supposed to get
a reply today to our request

80
00:10:27.679 --> 00:10:29.399
to build a shelter here?

81
00:10:29.479 --> 00:10:31.439
Yes.

82
00:10:31.599 --> 00:10:33.959
The answer is the same.

83
00:10:33.999 --> 00:10:35.599
Request denied.

84
00:10:37.119 --> 00:10:41.039
Well. if anything happens.
at least we've got our windbreakers.

85
00:10:41.119 --> 00:10:45.279
I'm bitterly aware of this. Engen.

86
00:10:45.359 --> 00:10:48.599
but I've tried everything.
Request after request.

87
00:10:48.679 --> 00:10:53.179
All denied.
Both here and at the main battery.

88
00:10:59.159 --> 00:11:02.359
Is the Commander
worried about the headlines?

89
00:11:04.599 --> 00:11:06.999
Do you think something could happen?

90
00:11:47.799 --> 00:11:51.199
COMMANDER'S RESIDENCE. OSCARSBORG

91
00:12:01.639 --> 00:12:03.279
Here you go.

92
00:12:04.719 --> 00:12:06.439
Good boy. Peik.

93
00:12:28.679 --> 00:12:32.159
Mother called. She's staying
at the farm a few more days.

94
00:12:32.239 --> 00:12:33.799
I see.

95
00:12:37.359 --> 00:12:41.599
I'm done with this room.
but I was wondering about these.

96
00:12:41.679 --> 00:12:45.639
Do you want these? Military textbooks?
You won't need those ...

97
00:12:45.719 --> 00:12:49.319
We don't need to do this now.
The move still a long way away.

98
00:12:49.399 --> 00:12:51.479
Not at your speed.

99
00:12:57.879 --> 00:12:59.359
Hello!

100
00:13:00.119 --> 00:13:01.959
Hello.

101
00:13:06.039 --> 00:13:08.079
Did you give him sausages again?

102
00:13:09.399 --> 00:13:10.799
No.

103
00:13:10.879 --> 00:13:13.999
Savoury food upsets his stomach
You know that.

104
00:13:37.319 --> 00:13:39.479
Borghild?

105
00:13:40.439 --> 00:13:43.719
-Borghild?
-What?

106
00:13:43.799 --> 00:13:45.399
Come here.

107
00:13:52.039 --> 00:13:53.919
Do your remember this?

108
00:13:56.959 --> 00:13:59.119
You were determined.

109
00:14:00.919 --> 00:14:02.839
Stubborn.

110
00:14:06.079 --> 00:14:08.199
I wonder who I got that from.

111
00:14:18.999 --> 00:14:21.479
I remember being thrilled here.

112
00:14:22.679 --> 00:14:25.239
We were playing cards. right?

113
00:14:25.319 --> 00:14:28.039
I remember. I won every time.

114
00:14:28.119 --> 00:14:30.879
I didn't realise you let me win.

115
00:14:30.959 --> 00:14:33.199
And I was so proud. because ...

116
00:14:36.359 --> 00:14:38.999
Mother said she'd call.

117
00:14:48.839 --> 00:14:51.199
-Eriksen.
<i>- This is Unneberg.</i>

118
00:14:51.279 --> 00:14:53.399
<i>We have new intelligence.</i>

119
00:14:53.479 --> 00:14:57.979
<i>There is a large German naval force
heading north from Denmark.</i>

120
00:14:59.679 --> 00:15:01.839
When did you receive this?

121
00:15:01.919 --> 00:15:04.999
<i>HQ received it a few hours ago.</i>

122
00:15:05.079 --> 00:15:09.579
-Hours ago?
<i>-Yes. But we were just informed now.</i>

123
00:15:09.719 --> 00:15:13.679
-Did they say anything else?
<i>-They're concerned.</i>

124
00:15:13.759 --> 00:15:18.259
<i>They fear a clash between German
and British ships in Norwegian waters.</i>

125
00:15:18.679 --> 00:15:23.159
<i>If this escalates. we'll have to
use force to assert our sovereignty.</i>

126
00:15:24.079 --> 00:15:25.839
Right.

127
00:15:28.599 --> 00:15:32.359
Unneberg. call an officer's meeting.
Right away.

128
00:15:32.439 --> 00:15:34.079
<i>Roger that.</i>

129
00:15:42.199 --> 00:15:43.959
What is it?

130
00:16:15.119 --> 00:16:16.759
Signal Corps.

131
00:16:17.679 --> 00:16:19.119
Yes.

132
00:16:20.599 --> 00:16:22.959
Yes. Repeat that?

133
00:16:24.999 --> 00:16:27.719
Roger that. Thank you.

134
00:16:27.799 --> 00:16:31.959
-Yes. Unneberg?
-It's not just the Germans out there.

135
00:16:32.039 --> 00:16:35.119
The Brits have
four cruisers and nine destroyers

136
00:16:35.199 --> 00:16:38.319
with orders to attack
the German northbound fleet.

137
00:16:41.239 --> 00:16:45.739
Have we received any orders
on how to conduct ourselves?

138
00:16:46.199 --> 00:16:47.839
No.

139
00:16:55.279 --> 00:16:59.599
If English or German ships
enter Norwegian waters.

140
00:16:59.679 --> 00:17:02.279
the government surely has to react?

141
00:17:02.359 --> 00:17:06.859
Not necessarily. Nygaardsvold will do
anything to avoid being drawn into the war.

142
00:17:07.359 --> 00:17:09.679
They have to assert Norwegian neutrality!

143
00:17:09.759 --> 00:17:13.399
Not if that means
conflict with the English.

144
00:17:13.479 --> 00:17:16.439
We have to be prepared. regardless.

145
00:17:16.599 --> 00:17:18.439
Has anyone seen Sødem?

146
00:17:18.599 --> 00:17:21.319
-Colonel!
-No. we haven't got hold of him.

147
00:17:21.399 --> 00:17:25.239
One of our boats in the outer Oslofjord
has launched a flare.

148
00:17:25.319 --> 00:17:27.959
-What colour?
-Red.

149
00:17:30.119 --> 00:17:32.279
-Captain.
-Thank you.

150
00:17:33.079 --> 00:17:37.479
The naval command at Horten reports
ships approaching at Rauøy.

151
00:17:37.639 --> 00:17:40.199
-What kind of ships?
-It doesn't say.

152
00:17:40.279 --> 00:17:44.779
-What about nationality?
-The message is unclear and lacks detail.

153
00:17:45.119 --> 00:17:48.599
They could be merchant ships
going north for some reason.

154
00:17:48.679 --> 00:17:51.879
-Are they past the outer defences?
-Yes.

155
00:17:51.959 --> 00:17:55.319
That means they have entered
our territorial waters.

156
00:17:56.839 --> 00:18:01.339
-When was the observation made?
-At 23:46. Four minutes ago.

157
00:18:08.879 --> 00:18:11.919
Colonel! The Commander at Rauøy.

158
00:18:14.439 --> 00:18:16.919
Put it on speaker. line two.

159
00:18:22.959 --> 00:18:24.959
-This is Eriksen.
<i>- Hello.</i>

160
00:18:25.039 --> 00:18:27.919
<i>We've just observed an unidentified ship.</i>

161
00:18:28.959 --> 00:18:31.679
<i>It's crossed the defence line.</i>

162
00:18:32.239 --> 00:18:33.959
Is it a warship?

163
00:18:33.999 --> 00:18:38.279
<i>The fog is so thick.
it's hard to see anything.</i>

164
00:18:39.959 --> 00:18:44.359
<i>-But it sounded fucking massive.</i>
-Wasn't the defence line mined?

165
00:18:46.399 --> 00:18:50.319
<i>No. we were ordered to stand by.
The fjord was clear.</i>

166
00:18:50.399 --> 00:18:54.479
<i>But ... we did fire a warning shot.</i>

167
00:18:54.639 --> 00:18:57.039
But it didn't stop?

168
00:18:57.119 --> 00:19:01.619
<i>It just glided past in the fog like
a ghost ship. without returning fire.</i>

169
00:19:05.039 --> 00:19:09.359
<i>They're in the Oslofjord
and could be headed towards you.</i>

170
00:19:09.439 --> 00:19:12.359
-Nationality?
<i>-No idea.</i>

171
00:19:12.439 --> 00:19:14.879
<i>We saw no flags or anything.</i>

172
00:19:16.839 --> 00:19:18.839
Did you see anything else?

173
00:19:18.919 --> 00:19:21.599
<i>We think there might be another ship.</i>

174
00:19:21.679 --> 00:19:24.879
<i>We'll report any further sightings.</i>

175
00:19:26.959 --> 00:19:30.959
Unneberg get me Smith-Johannsen
or someone else at HQ.

176
00:19:33.479 --> 00:19:36.279
It could be the Brits laying mines again.

177
00:19:36.359 --> 00:19:40.639
Odd for a British ship
to not identify itself.

178
00:19:40.719 --> 00:19:45.219
If they're headed our way.
they'll pass Horten in about an hour.

179
00:19:47.759 --> 00:19:52.119
If they get past Horten. they'll pass
the observation post at Filtvet.

180
00:19:54.919 --> 00:19:58.919
From there.
they'll reach us in twenty minutes.

181
00:20:01.399 --> 00:20:05.899
-Will HQ issue a mobilisation order?
-We have to be prepared for that.

182
00:20:06.039 --> 00:20:10.539
-And we have to prepare to lay mines.
-We don't know if it's a warship.

183
00:20:13.119 --> 00:20:15.639
Colonel. Smith-Johannsen in Horten.

184
00:20:16.839 --> 00:20:18.159
Line one. Colonel.

185
00:20:18.239 --> 00:20:20.399
-On loudspeaker?
-Yes.

186
00:20:20.479 --> 00:20:23.159
-Speaker.
-Eriksen.

187
00:20:23.239 --> 00:20:25.639
<i>Admiral Smith-Johannsen here.</i>

188
00:20:25.719 --> 00:20:29.239
What are our orders
in regards to the foreign ship?

189
00:20:29.319 --> 00:20:32.159
<i>No change in standing orders as of yet.</i>

190
00:20:32.239 --> 00:20:35.959
<i>We're awaiting an imminent decision
from the government.</i>

191
00:20:36.039 --> 00:20:39.039
-Have you issued a mobilisation alert?
<i>- No.</i>

192
00:20:39.119 --> 00:20:41.879
-Are we laying mines?
<i>- No.</i>

193
00:20:41.959 --> 00:20:46.459
<i>But this is a violation of our neutrality.
A most serious situation.</i>

194
00:20:47.399 --> 00:20:49.599
<i>We must act with great care.</i>

195
00:20:49.679 --> 00:20:54.179
<i>We don't want to be dragged into
the war due to rash decisions.</i>

196
00:20:54.479 --> 00:20:57.799
-So what are our orders?
<i>- To stand by.</i>

197
00:20:57.879 --> 00:21:00.479
-Stand by?
<i>- Yes. For now.</i>

198
00:21:00.639 --> 00:21:03.719
Do you know the nationality
or type of ship. at least?

199
00:21:03.799 --> 00:21:08.299
<i>No. There might have been a clash
between English and German ships.</i>

200
00:21:09.959 --> 00:21:14.399
<i>and that the observed ships
were on the losing side.</i>

201
00:21:14.479 --> 00:21:17.279
<i>and are seeking refuge
in the Oslo fjord.</i>

202
00:21:17.359 --> 00:21:21.859
Ships from nations at war must identify
themselves if they cross our defence lines.

203
00:21:22.399 --> 00:21:26.239
<i>-I'm aware of the neutrality regulations.</i>
-Yes. yes.

204
00:21:26.319 --> 00:21:29.279
<i>The aim is to keep Norway out of the war.</i>

205
00:21:30.679 --> 00:21:34.119
<i>Your mission is to stay alert
and keep your head cool.</i>

206
00:21:35.479 --> 00:21:39.199
-I see.
<i>- No rash decisions.</i>

207
00:21:39.799 --> 00:21:42.479
<i>- Nothing further to report.</i>
-Roger that.

208
00:21:56.079 --> 00:22:00.579
Are we not laying mines?
They don't see the ship as a threat?

209
00:22:02.039 --> 00:22:06.539
If the warship is headed our way.
they'll be here in two hours.

210
00:22:10.839 --> 00:22:14.119
From us to Oslo ...

211
00:22:15.239 --> 00:22:16.759
Half an hour.

212
00:22:32.279 --> 00:22:36.639
Issue the following command
to every station:

213
00:22:36.719 --> 00:22:38.159
Ready for battle.

214
00:22:41.639 --> 00:22:44.679
I repeat. ready for battle. Berntsen.

215
00:22:44.759 --> 00:22:48.719
Bonsak? Until Sødem returns.
you're in charge oft the main battery.

216
00:22:48.799 --> 00:22:52.079
Høie. Head to the orograph.
Enger. Get across the fjord.

217
00:22:52.159 --> 00:22:56.159
Report when the l battery is ready.
Get the trainee officers to help.

218
00:22:56.239 --> 00:22:58.439
Berntsen. Berntsen!

219
00:22:58.599 --> 00:23:01.399
Send Anderssen to the torpedo battery.

220
00:23:01.479 --> 00:23:04.079
Unneberg: call the police chief in Drøbak.

221
00:23:04.159 --> 00:23:07.279
Drøbak must be evacuated and blacked out.

222
00:23:11.119 --> 00:23:14.399
Colonel!
What about the civilians in the fortress?

223
00:23:16.439 --> 00:23:19.199
We're not evacuating. Let them sleep.

224
00:23:19.279 --> 00:23:20.839
Colonel!

225
00:23:22.479 --> 00:23:26.919
-What will our men think ...
-I can't have civilians running around.

226
00:23:26.959 --> 00:23:29.759
I can't have chaos here now.

227
00:23:30.839 --> 00:23:33.479
-Report when you hear anything
-Colonel.

228
00:23:34.079 --> 00:23:38.039
Alarm! Assemble by the canon post-haste!

229
00:23:38.119 --> 00:23:40.959
This is not a drill!

230
00:24:12.799 --> 00:24:14.359
Fall in!

231
00:24:14.439 --> 00:24:17.879
Sergeant Rækken
is in charge of readying the cannon.

232
00:24:17.959 --> 00:24:22.459
Sergeant Strøm. privates Jarskog.
Jacobsen. Eliasen. down in the depot.

233
00:24:23.919 --> 00:24:26.039
-Off you go.
-Yes. lieutenant.

234
00:24:42.079 --> 00:24:43.599
Bonsak!

235
00:24:48.239 --> 00:24:51.639
-Are all trained personnel present?
-Yes.

236
00:24:51.719 --> 00:24:53.399
I want cannon two manned. too.

237
00:24:54.639 --> 00:24:56.919
We've barely got enough to man one.

238
00:24:57.839 --> 00:25:01.759
Without two cannons.
we'll be helpless if something happens.

239
00:25:05.759 --> 00:25:10.259
Divide the trained crew and
add non-combatants as needed.

240
00:25:12.479 --> 00:25:14.479
-Non-combatants?
-Yes.

241
00:25:14.639 --> 00:25:19.139
Orderlies. comms. cooks. anyone.

242
00:25:19.639 --> 00:25:21.679
With all due respect. Colonel.

243
00:25:22.959 --> 00:25:25.999
These people have hardly seen a cannon.

244
00:25:26.079 --> 00:25:28.199
We have no choice.

245
00:25:28.279 --> 00:25:31.279
You have to train them to be artillerists.

246
00:25:32.479 --> 00:25:34.959
And you have to do it now.

247
00:25:35.039 --> 00:25:37.639
-See to it.
-Colonel.

248
00:25:39.399 --> 00:25:40.959
Sergeant Strøm!

249
00:26:07.079 --> 00:26:09.719
-Any news?
-No.

250
00:26:36.999 --> 00:26:38.759
Anderssen.

251
00:26:40.759 --> 00:26:43.159
-Is the battery ready?
-Soon.

252
00:26:43.239 --> 00:26:47.739
Set to vertical impact. Depth: 2.5 metres.
Distance: 425 metres.

253
00:26:49.919 --> 00:26:51.839
Good.

254
00:26:51.919 --> 00:26:54.799
Do we know anything more about the ships?

255
00:26:54.879 --> 00:26:57.599
We've had no new information.

256
00:27:00.599 --> 00:27:05.099
It's been an hour. and we've still not
received a mobilisation order.

257
00:27:06.119 --> 00:27:08.239
Colonel. Captain.

258
00:27:08.319 --> 00:27:12.599
-We've checked the pressure.
-Are the warheads out?

259
00:27:14.719 --> 00:27:17.079
-Not yet.
-Do it.

260
00:27:18.479 --> 00:27:20.199
Shall we arm them as well?

261
00:27:21.279 --> 00:27:22.719
Yes.

262
00:27:22.799 --> 00:27:24.479
-All of them?
-Yes.

263
00:27:28.199 --> 00:27:30.119
-See to it. Bexrud.
-Roger.

264
00:27:33.399 --> 00:27:34.999
Birger!

265
00:27:37.959 --> 00:27:40.959
We can't fire warning shots with torpedoes.

266
00:27:42.279 --> 00:27:46.779
If we attack a foreign ship with live ammo.
are we neutral. or are we the aggressor?

267
00:27:47.959 --> 00:27:50.479
Captain! Torpedoes ready.

268
00:27:50.639 --> 00:27:52.759
Carry out.

269
00:27:52.839 --> 00:27:57.339
I just want to make sure
we're doing the right thing.

270
00:27:57.639 --> 00:27:59.399
Listen. Andreas.

271
00:27:59.479 --> 00:28:03.679
If a warship has come all the way here ...

272
00:28:03.759 --> 00:28:06.479
Is it not they who violate our neutrality?

273
00:28:07.919 --> 00:28:10.639
Is it not they who are the aggressor?

274
00:28:10.719 --> 00:28:13.399
But this can't be an attack!

275
00:28:13.479 --> 00:28:16.599
We've had no reports of hostile actions.

276
00:28:19.199 --> 00:28:21.439
No one has fired on us.

277
00:28:21.599 --> 00:28:25.639
There's no mobilisation order
or declaration of war!

278
00:28:25.719 --> 00:28:27.719
We're not at war.

279
00:28:29.319 --> 00:28:32.399
Norway has not been at war
for over 120 years.

280
00:28:32.479 --> 00:28:34.079
No.

281
00:29:13.439 --> 00:29:16.679
-Sødem!
-Colonel!

282
00:29:16.759 --> 00:29:21.159
-Where have you been?
-On the mainland. like you ordered.

283
00:29:21.239 --> 00:29:23.879
I've issued a "ready for battle" order.

284
00:29:23.959 --> 00:29:25.479
Battle?

285
00:29:25.639 --> 00:29:29.919
-There are foreign ships in the fjord.
-I'll man the main battery.

286
00:29:29.959 --> 00:29:32.319
Bonsak manned it at midnight.

287
00:29:32.399 --> 00:29:36.599
And I've ordered the non-combatants
to man the cannons.

288
00:29:37.399 --> 00:29:41.899
-Non-combatants manning the cannons?
-Yes. So go and help Bonsak.

289
00:29:42.799 --> 00:29:47.299
I'll be out soon
and take charge if anything happens.

290
00:29:47.599 --> 00:29:52.079
But you're in charge of the whole fortress.

291
00:29:52.159 --> 00:29:55.159
Your place is not out by the guns.

292
00:29:55.239 --> 00:29:56.919
It is now.

293
00:30:40.079 --> 00:30:42.319
Are there warships out on the fjord?

294
00:30:44.279 --> 00:30:48.279
It's unlikely they come up here.
They have to pass the base at Horten.

295
00:30:48.359 --> 00:30:50.679
They'll stop them there.

296
00:30:50.759 --> 00:30:53.439
So why have you issued
a "ready to battle" order?

297
00:30:59.079 --> 00:31:01.479
Because we have to ber prepared.

298
00:31:05.959 --> 00:31:07.799
Alright.

299
00:31:09.159 --> 00:31:12.119
I will man one of the phones
at the switchboard.

300
00:31:12.199 --> 00:31:14.359
No.

301
00:31:14.439 --> 00:31:16.319
What I need you to do ...

302
00:31:18.159 --> 00:31:20.279
... is to go home ...

303
00:31:20.359 --> 00:31:23.319
... and look after Peik. Can you do that?

304
00:31:43.479 --> 00:31:45.079
Here. Let me.

305
00:31:53.719 --> 00:31:55.839
Sleep fully clothed.

306
00:31:58.479 --> 00:32:00.079
Go home.

307
00:32:04.479 --> 00:32:06.119
Be careful.

308
00:32:27.439 --> 00:32:31.939
We were ordered to stand by.
but we got no new orders after midnight.

309
00:32:33.639 --> 00:32:36.039
And how did you interpret that?

310
00:32:38.799 --> 00:32:42.839
That the government
wanted to remain neutral.

311
00:32:49.119 --> 00:32:50.639
Yes.

312
00:32:55.839 --> 00:32:58.319
Just a moment. Eriksen.

313
00:33:28.159 --> 00:33:32.659
Captains Enger and Sødem.
thank you for making time for us.

314
00:33:35.279 --> 00:33:39.159
Since there are
conflicting reports on this event.

315
00:33:39.239 --> 00:33:42.999
we wanted to hear these
gentlemen's explanations. as well.

316
00:33:43.759 --> 00:33:48.259
Let's start with the main battery.
Sødem. you were in charge there.

317
00:33:49.719 --> 00:33:53.839
Colonel Eriksen just told us
he took over command.

318
00:33:54.799 --> 00:33:56.719
What are your thoughts on that?

319
00:34:00.799 --> 00:34:05.299
The commanding officer should not be
in such an exposed position.

320
00:34:07.039 --> 00:34:11.539
It was highly irregular and strange.

321
00:34:11.959 --> 00:34:16.039
He should never have been
out there with us that night.

322
00:34:16.119 --> 00:34:20.619
Did the Colonel not have faith in Sødem?

323
00:34:20.999 --> 00:34:23.679
He'd only been with us for a week.

324
00:34:23.759 --> 00:34:28.199
He lacked. like many of his
fellow officers. practical experience.

325
00:34:29.399 --> 00:34:32.719
I wanted to ensure
any shots would be well aimed.

326
00:34:32.799 --> 00:34:35.679
But you agree that it is irregular?

327
00:34:37.119 --> 00:34:41.439
There were many things
that had to be irregular that night.

328
00:34:44.959 --> 00:34:46.399
Fire!

329
00:34:47.719 --> 00:34:49.399
Get down here!

330
00:34:49.959 --> 00:34:54.459
MAIN BATTERY. OSCARSBORG - 03:21

331
00:34:57.479 --> 00:35:01.759
You're moving too fucking slowly.
to speak plainly.

332
00:35:03.279 --> 00:35:07.779
We have to get the ammunition
from the carrier to the gun much faster.

333
00:35:09.759 --> 00:35:14.259
Lower the barrel 3.5 degrees right away!
This is fucking essential!

334
00:35:16.719 --> 00:35:18.359
Listen.

335
00:35:19.759 --> 00:35:24.159
Half of you have never
seen a cannon fire before.

336
00:35:24.839 --> 00:35:27.959
It's going to be fucking loud.
let me tell you.

337
00:35:28.039 --> 00:35:32.539
If we have to fire. remain at your
designated places. Don't panic.

338
00:35:33.279 --> 00:35:37.779
The pressure is immense. so before we
fire. everyone needs to be on their toes.

339
00:35:38.359 --> 00:35:42.859
If the ships are hostile. we're the only
ones who can stop them!

340
00:35:46.119 --> 00:35:47.999
Is that understood?

341
00:35:48.079 --> 00:35:50.239
-Is that understood?
-Yes. lieutenant!

342
00:35:50.319 --> 00:35:52.639
And again. One more time.

343
00:35:55.879 --> 00:35:57.439
Bonsak.

344
00:36:01.439 --> 00:36:05.939
-How is it going?
-It's still too slow.

345
00:36:06.959 --> 00:36:09.399
We've been at it for two hours.

346
00:36:09.479 --> 00:36:11.679
We haven't had any news still?

347
00:36:38.839 --> 00:36:43.079
The last sighting was
three hours ago. here.

348
00:36:43.159 --> 00:36:47.279
If they were headed here.
they would've passed Horten ages ago.

349
00:36:47.359 --> 00:36:51.159
We would have seen them an hour ago.
And we haven't.

350
00:36:54.079 --> 00:36:57.239
Colonel? Horten on line one.

351
00:36:58.959 --> 00:37:00.919
Berntsen. put it on speaker.

352
00:37:03.839 --> 00:37:07.119
-This is Eriksen.
<i>- Admiral Smith-Johannsen here.</i>

353
00:37:09.039 --> 00:37:12.479
<i>It was rather hectic
for a while there. Eriksen.</i>

354
00:37:12.639 --> 00:37:14.959
<i>But it's calmed down.</i>

355
00:37:14.999 --> 00:37:18.959
<i>I just spoke to Major Ferden
at outer Oslofjord fortress.</i>

356
00:37:19.039 --> 00:37:21.959
<i>- He agrees with me.</i>
-About what?

357
00:37:22.719 --> 00:37:26.679
<i>That the situation is not
as urgent as we thought.</i>

358
00:37:26.759 --> 00:37:29.959
<i>The ships were probably fleeing a battle.</i>

359
00:37:30.479 --> 00:37:32.959
<i>They were seeking refuge.</i>

360
00:37:35.279 --> 00:37:39.199
-Where are they now?
<i>- No longer in the fjord. we assume.</i>

361
00:37:39.999 --> 00:37:44.499
<i>It's been hours since the last sighting.
No other news to report.</i>

362
00:37:48.319 --> 00:37:49.959
Roger that.

363
00:37:55.799 --> 00:37:58.399
Smith-Johannsen thinks the danger is past?

364
00:37:58.479 --> 00:38:00.719
Thank you.

365
00:38:00.799 --> 00:38:02.759
Let's hope he's right.

366
00:38:02.839 --> 00:38:07.199
We could've ended up in a war
with a country we sympathise with.

367
00:38:07.279 --> 00:38:10.799
I guess we'll never know what ship it was.

368
00:38:10.879 --> 00:38:12.639
Coffee. Colonel?

369
00:38:12.719 --> 00:38:16.159
Maybe it's just as well. For everyone.

370
00:38:17.599 --> 00:38:21.079
Could've been anything.
English. German. French.

371
00:38:21.159 --> 00:38:23.759
-Norwegian.
-Anything's possible.

372
00:38:27.839 --> 00:38:30.639
Shall we dismiss the men from the guns?

373
00:38:32.639 --> 00:38:36.879
Dismiss half.
We'll take turns throughout the night.

374
00:38:36.959 --> 00:38:38.879
Colonel!

375
00:38:38.959 --> 00:38:43.459
It's the observation post at Filtvet.
They've sighted a warship.

376
00:38:45.759 --> 00:38:47.399
Nationality?

377
00:38:47.479 --> 00:38:49.079
They don't know.

378
00:38:50.839 --> 00:38:54.839
Sødem. assemble the men
and ready the main battery.

379
00:38:54.919 --> 00:38:58.479
How did they get to Filtvet?
We'll see them any minute.

380
00:38:58.639 --> 00:39:02.319
Could it be the same ship
Rauøy saw at midnight?

381
00:39:02.399 --> 00:39:05.919
-Maybe it hid in the fog ...
-Commander?

382
00:39:05.959 --> 00:39:08.879
New message from Filtvet.
It's not one warship.

383
00:39:08.959 --> 00:39:10.439
It's five.

384
00:39:11.199 --> 00:39:15.679
Three heavily armed cruisers.
They just passed them.

385
00:39:21.479 --> 00:39:24.959
How the hell did five warships
get past the main base?

386
00:39:25.039 --> 00:39:29.079
-Are the guns loaded with live ammo?
-No.

387
00:39:29.159 --> 00:39:33.119
The ammunition used
depends on the type of vessel.

388
00:39:33.199 --> 00:39:36.319
-Do we fire a warning shot?
-No. live ammunition.

389
00:39:36.399 --> 00:39:39.599
345 kg brisance grenades. Get to it!

390
00:39:39.679 --> 00:39:41.439
Yes. sir.

391
00:39:41.599 --> 00:39:45.879
Høie. get up to the orograph.
Report as soon as you see anything.

392
00:39:45.959 --> 00:39:50.459
-How are the non-combatants doing?
-I hope they've got the essentials.

393
00:39:50.639 --> 00:39:53.479
If we miss. we'll blow up Drøbak harbour!

394
00:39:55.719 --> 00:39:57.279
Granum!

395
00:39:59.439 --> 00:40:01.719
What are our orders?

396
00:40:01.799 --> 00:40:04.839
Colonel! From the torpedo battery.

397
00:40:04.919 --> 00:40:07.639
Captain Anderssen
insists on a direct order.

398
00:40:07.719 --> 00:40:12.079
-Are we firing?
-Tell him. yes. we are firing.

399
00:40:12.159 --> 00:40:16.439
In lieu of direct orders.
we are to follow the neutrality protocol.

400
00:40:16.599 --> 00:40:21.079
-That dictates we fire a warning shot.
-A warning shot has already been fired.

401
00:40:21.159 --> 00:40:25.659
-From Rauøy.
-That's not valid still! Not here!

402
00:40:25.839 --> 00:40:30.339
A warning shot doesn't count
for the whole fjord for all time!

403
00:40:30.799 --> 00:40:34.719
Rauøy fired three hours ago.
and on one ship. not five!

404
00:40:34.799 --> 00:40:38.959
That was 40 km further out!
We don't know if these are the same ships!

405
00:40:39.039 --> 00:40:43.539
Once ships pass us.
they're in Oslo in half an hour.

406
00:40:43.839 --> 00:40:45.639
No one else can stop them.

407
00:40:45.719 --> 00:40:50.219
This is irregular. We have to confer with
the CO before we use live ammo!

408
00:40:50.719 --> 00:40:53.479
You're damn right we're using live ammo!

409
00:41:01.399 --> 00:41:03.199
Listen. Sødem.

410
00:41:04.319 --> 00:41:06.039
I know the rules.

411
00:41:07.479 --> 00:41:10.199
This is not the time for hesitation.

412
00:41:12.159 --> 00:41:13.799
Is that understood?

413
00:41:41.079 --> 00:41:42.679
Load up!

414
00:41:57.159 --> 00:41:59.839
Gun 1 ready!

415
00:42:04.639 --> 00:42:07.239
Gun 2 ready!

416
00:42:21.399 --> 00:42:23.239
Do you see anything?

417
00:42:24.479 --> 00:42:25.999
No.

418
00:43:01.199 --> 00:43:02.719
Do you hear that?

419
00:44:21.039 --> 00:44:23.399
Ready the guns.

420
00:44:23.479 --> 00:44:25.799
Ready the guns!

421
00:44:25.879 --> 00:44:27.319
Ready!

422
00:44:33.279 --> 00:44:35.719
Colonel! I can't determine distance!

423
00:44:36.799 --> 00:44:38.879
What range is the target?

424
00:44:43.079 --> 00:44:46.799
I repeat. what is the distance to target?

425
00:44:46.879 --> 00:44:49.319
Høie. give us the correct distance.

426
00:44:51.039 --> 00:44:54.159
I can't see the distance
markers in the fog!

427
00:44:55.359 --> 00:44:57.279
I can hardly see anything.

428
00:44:58.759 --> 00:45:00.879
What range is the target?

429
00:45:01.719 --> 00:45:05.959
-Høie!
-The target is not visible from the gun!

430
00:45:06.039 --> 00:45:08.119
Distance 1800 metres.

431
00:45:09.919 --> 00:45:12.279
No. that's too far.

432
00:45:16.879 --> 00:45:20.919
-Distance: 1400 metres.
-Are you going by eye?

433
00:45:22.199 --> 00:45:26.699
It's inside Storskjær.
The distance is 1400 metres.

434
00:45:27.839 --> 00:45:30.639
Set to 1400 metres!

435
00:45:30.719 --> 00:45:32.719
1400 metres!

436
00:45:44.359 --> 00:45:46.159
Do you see the nationality?

437
00:45:47.479 --> 00:45:49.079
No.

438
00:45:50.239 --> 00:45:52.039
There are more ships behind it.

439
00:45:53.639 --> 00:45:55.879
They're not in attack formation!

440
00:45:58.279 --> 00:46:00.399
There are lots of people on board!

441
00:46:09.919 --> 00:46:12.319
We're ready to fire!

442
00:46:21.839 --> 00:46:23.959
Open fire.

443
00:46:24.039 --> 00:46:26.279
Cannon one!

444
00:46:26.359 --> 00:46:28.319
Fire!

445
00:46:33.959 --> 00:46:35.679
Cannon two!

446
00:46:35.759 --> 00:46:37.359
Fire!

447
00:46:59.999 --> 00:47:01.999
Down. down. down!

448
00:47:11.199 --> 00:47:13.199
Cannon one!

449
00:47:13.279 --> 00:47:15.039
Fire!

450
00:47:18.719 --> 00:47:20.239
Ready!

451
00:47:25.719 --> 00:47:28.479
-Cannon one!
-Fire!

452
00:47:47.599 --> 00:47:50.359
It's just a scratch!
Get a hold of yourself!

453
00:47:50.439 --> 00:47:54.239
-Bonsak! Get him to the infirmary.
-Strøm. Infirmary.

454
00:47:54.319 --> 00:47:58.079
And ready the guns.
There are more ships in the fjord.

455
00:48:14.199 --> 00:48:16.159
<i>- Unneberg.</i>
-Torpedo battery.

456
00:48:16.239 --> 00:48:17.799
<i>Yes.</i>

457
00:48:22.039 --> 00:48:24.319
<i>- Yes. Anderssen.</i>
-One incoming vessel.

458
00:48:24.399 --> 00:48:27.359
<i>- Repeat.</i>
-One incoming vessel.

459
00:48:27.439 --> 00:48:30.479
-Do you know the nationality?
<i>- No.</i>

460
00:48:30.639 --> 00:48:34.439
You will see it soon. Ready to fire.

461
00:48:35.599 --> 00:48:37.999
-Ready to fire!
-Yes. Captain!

462
00:48:38.079 --> 00:48:39.959
Ready to fire!

463
00:48:41.999 --> 00:48:43.959
Safety bolts out!

464
00:48:51.999 --> 00:48:53.839
Vessel sighted!

465
00:49:09.959 --> 00:49:12.879
Target in sight! Torpedo one!

466
00:49:26.199 --> 00:49:28.999
-Ready torpedo two!
-Aye aye. Captain!

467
00:49:29.079 --> 00:49:31.319
Safety bolts. out!

468
00:49:33.119 --> 00:49:35.399
Target in sight!

469
00:49:35.479 --> 00:49:37.039
Torpedo two!

470
00:50:47.999 --> 00:50:50.479
The other ships are retreating.

471
00:50:51.279 --> 00:50:55.039
We're not ready to fire.
but we're working on it.

472
00:50:57.239 --> 00:51:00.959
We don't fire on fleeing ships.

473
00:51:01.039 --> 00:51:05.539
We've asserted our neutrality.
The fortress has served its purpose.

474
00:51:36.199 --> 00:51:40.699
Unneberg.
Has there been a declaration of war?

475
00:51:42.239 --> 00:51:43.959
No.

476
00:51:46.079 --> 00:51:49.359
-Has the mobilisation order been issued?
-No.

477
00:51:50.319 --> 00:51:52.599
-The nationality ...?
- No.

478
00:51:54.239 --> 00:51:56.799
The ship fired on the fortress.

479
00:51:58.239 --> 00:52:02.679
But they also fired on Drøbak.

480
00:52:02.759 --> 00:52:04.759
Several houses are alight.

481
00:52:13.399 --> 00:52:15.919
Our house is on fire.

482
00:52:15.959 --> 00:52:17.959
We're going to lose everything.

483
00:52:19.159 --> 00:52:20.959
What about Lucie and the kids?

484
00:52:20.999 --> 00:52:22.639
They ...

485
00:52:23.799 --> 00:52:25.599
They got out.

486
00:52:25.679 --> 00:52:27.959
I think. I hope.

487
00:52:32.199 --> 00:52:33.919
Is Borghild safe?

488
00:52:34.959 --> 00:52:37.359
Several houses here on the island were hit.

489
00:52:48.319 --> 00:52:49.999
Borghild?

490
00:52:56.439 --> 00:52:57.999
Borghild?

491
00:52:59.759 --> 00:53:01.239
Borghild?

492
00:53:33.159 --> 00:53:35.079
Borghild?

493
00:53:35.159 --> 00:53:36.679
Borghild!

494
00:53:38.399 --> 00:53:41.199
-Are you injured?
-No. I did as you asked.

495
00:53:41.279 --> 00:53:43.799
But I heard the guns. so I had to see.

496
00:53:43.879 --> 00:53:46.999
And when I opened the door ...
I tried to stop him!

497
00:53:47.079 --> 00:53:49.319
But he was so quick. and now ...

498
00:53:49.399 --> 00:53:53.899
I've looked everywhere.
He's probably terrified!

499
00:53:54.399 --> 00:53:57.639
-You had a task.
-Yes. I ...

500
00:53:57.719 --> 00:54:01.319
-You were to remain in the house!
-I'm sorry.

501
00:54:01.399 --> 00:54:04.399
I have to be able to trust you.
Don't you get that?

502
00:55:20.599 --> 00:55:22.839
We have to help them.

503
00:55:24.079 --> 00:55:26.319
We have to help them. Father!

504
00:55:28.359 --> 00:55:31.439
We can't just watch. We have to help them.

505
00:55:31.599 --> 00:55:33.279
Borghild ...

506
00:55:52.199 --> 00:55:54.399
They're shouting in German.

507
00:55:54.479 --> 00:55:56.279
They're German soldiers.

508
00:56:42.079 --> 00:56:46.579
So that's how the German
warship Blücher was sunk.

509
00:56:47.679 --> 00:56:50.399
500 German soldiers lost their lives.

510
00:56:51.359 --> 00:56:54.319
This delayed the
invasion of Oslo by several hours.

511
00:56:54.399 --> 00:56:57.919
allowing the King and government to escape.

512
00:56:57.959 --> 00:57:02.459
For this. you were awarded
the War Cross with Sword.

513
00:57:02.719 --> 00:57:07.219
But there are some other matters
we'd like to discuss. Eriksen.

514
00:57:12.479 --> 00:57:14.159
There were ...

515
00:57:15.719 --> 00:57:17.639
... other ships.

516
00:57:19.439 --> 00:57:22.359
Two shots from the main battery.

517
00:57:25.479 --> 00:57:29.979
Eriksen. why ... didn't you fire more?

518
00:57:32.479 --> 00:57:34.119
More?

519
00:57:35.359 --> 00:57:38.759
There were more ships.
Why didn't you fire at them?

520
00:57:38.839 --> 00:57:40.799
They were fleeing.

521
00:57:42.359 --> 00:57:46.859
Right. This leads us to the main question
regarding the surrender of the fort.

522
00:57:48.319 --> 00:57:52.819
There are conflicting accounts
in the reports we've received.

523
00:57:55.919 --> 00:58:00.419
This Commission is looking into
whether the fort was surrendered too soon.

524
00:58:10.879 --> 00:58:13.199
Yes. I understand that. but ...

525
00:58:15.479 --> 00:58:17.119
... any new information ...

526
00:58:17.199 --> 00:58:19.159
Thanks for getting in touch.

527
00:58:19.239 --> 00:58:23.439
We have tried the Chief of Defence
and the Foreign Office.

528
00:58:23.599 --> 00:58:25.599
No reply.

529
00:58:46.199 --> 00:58:47.799
Colonel!

530
00:58:49.239 --> 00:58:52.919
Oslo High Command.
Major General Hvinden Haug.

531
00:58:52.959 --> 00:58:54.839
Put it through on line one.

532
00:58:56.199 --> 00:58:57.719
On speaker?

533
00:58:58.999 --> 00:59:00.999
-Yes.
-Speaker.

534
00:59:02.359 --> 00:59:04.159
Yes?

535
00:59:04.239 --> 00:59:08.599
<i>I hear Oscarsborg has sunk
a German battleship. Well done.</i>

536
00:59:10.119 --> 00:59:11.999
What's the situation presently?

537
00:59:12.079 --> 00:59:14.679
<i>The King and government have left Oslo.</i>

538
00:59:15.639 --> 00:59:17.799
<i>The military command too.</i>

539
00:59:18.919 --> 00:59:22.719
<i>The Germans have attacked
multiple Norwegian positions.</i>

540
00:59:22.799 --> 00:59:27.119
<i>Bergen. Trondheim.
Stavanger and Kristiansand.</i>

541
00:59:27.199 --> 00:59:29.279
<i>They have all fallen.</i>

542
00:59:33.959 --> 00:59:35.439
<i>Norway is at war.</i>

543
00:59:43.079 --> 00:59:46.079
<i>We expect the capital to fall shortly.</i>

544
00:59:46.159 --> 00:59:50.659
<i>German forces are on the way.
They landed at Fornebu not long ago.</i>

545
00:59:52.959 --> 00:59:55.879
-Uh ...
<i>- Yes. Eriksen?</i>

546
00:59:55.959 --> 00:59:59.799
I don't understand.
Wasn't the runway barricaded?

547
00:59:59.879 --> 01:00:01.239
<i>No.</i>

548
01:00:02.079 --> 01:00:05.159
-Has the mobilisation order been issued?
<i>- Yes.</i>

549
01:00:05.239 --> 01:00:08.999
When can we expect
the troops to be mobilised?

550
01:00:09.079 --> 01:00:11.439
<i>It could be several days.</i>

551
01:00:12.199 --> 01:00:13.959
Several days?

552
01:00:13.999 --> 01:00:18.499
<i>It was decided
to issue the order in the post.</i>

553
01:00:19.079 --> 01:00:21.239
In the post.

554
01:00:21.319 --> 01:00:23.079
<i>Yes. so ...</i>

555
01:00:24.839 --> 01:00:29.159
<i>So it will likely take a while
to mobilise the troops.</i>

556
01:00:31.479 --> 01:00:35.279
<i>So what do we do now?
What are our orders?</i>

557
01:00:36.319 --> 01:00:39.839
<i>English ships can come
to our aid at any point.</i>

558
01:00:40.839 --> 01:00:45.339
The general's orders are to
defend the forts as long as possible.

559
01:00:46.439 --> 01:00:48.439
What does that mean?

560
01:00:48.599 --> 01:00:51.039
<i>You ... have to do what you can.</i>

561
01:00:51.119 --> 01:00:53.199
I need reinforcements.

562
01:00:53.279 --> 01:00:56.799
To protect the fort
from assaults from land.

563
01:00:56.879 --> 01:00:59.159
<i>That will not be possible.</i>

564
01:00:59.239 --> 01:01:00.959
Is it impossible?

565
01:01:01.039 --> 01:01:02.639
<i>Eriksen ...</i>

566
01:01:05.639 --> 01:01:08.039
<i>Hold the fort as long as you are able.</i>

567
01:01:43.079 --> 01:01:44.599
Sødem.

568
01:01:45.959 --> 01:01:50.459
Give the recruits rifles.
Have Bonsak give them a crash course.

569
01:02:01.479 --> 01:02:04.079
Father? Father?

570
01:02:04.159 --> 01:02:05.959
-What?
-It's Kopås.

571
01:02:09.919 --> 01:02:11.639
-Yes.
<i>- This is Enger.</i>

572
01:02:11.719 --> 01:02:14.999
We have to expect
German attacks from land.

573
01:02:15.079 --> 01:02:16.799
Man all the posts.

574
01:02:16.879 --> 01:02:21.239
<i>We hear all the major cities have fallen.
What are our orders?</i>

575
01:02:21.319 --> 01:02:24.999
To hold the fort as long as possible.
We keep fighting.

576
01:02:25.079 --> 01:02:26.959
Yes. Roger that.

577
01:02:37.879 --> 01:02:41.279
Hansen. Holmbo.

578
01:02:41.359 --> 01:02:42.959
Henriksen.

579
01:02:44.119 --> 01:02:46.319
Bolt back. bolt forward.

580
01:02:46.399 --> 01:02:49.399
If you need to fire. the safety is here.

581
01:02:49.479 --> 01:02:53.979
Chamber. Bolt back. bolt forward.

582
01:02:54.319 --> 01:02:58.819
Chamber. lever. bolt back. bolt forward.

583
01:02:59.639 --> 01:03:01.959
This is the safety.

584
01:03:01.999 --> 01:03:05.319
Ammunition will be
distributed at the depot.

585
01:03:07.239 --> 01:03:09.839
Attention!

586
01:03:09.919 --> 01:03:11.879
Listen.

587
01:03:13.159 --> 01:03:15.399
We have been attacked.

588
01:03:15.479 --> 01:03:17.399
Norway is at war.

589
01:03:18.479 --> 01:03:20.599
But the fight is not over.

590
01:03:21.639 --> 01:03:26.139
Our orders are
to hold the fort as long as possible.

591
01:03:26.359 --> 01:03:30.859
We have to be prepared for
a German assault from the land.

592
01:03:34.039 --> 01:03:38.539
We have to spread out. take our positions
and prepare to defend the fort ...

593
01:04:01.839 --> 01:04:04.479
Faster! Come on!

594
01:04:14.199 --> 01:04:15.919
Stay here!

595
01:04:16.879 --> 01:04:18.719
Closer to the wall!

596
01:05:07.479 --> 01:05:10.079
Everyone to the tunnel magazine. Now!

597
01:05:10.159 --> 01:05:11.839
-Run!
-Come on!

598
01:05:11.919 --> 01:05:13.399
Hurry!

599
01:05:15.399 --> 01:05:17.239
Come on!

600
01:05:20.039 --> 01:05:21.759
Women and children first!

601
01:05:27.279 --> 01:05:30.359
Wait. wait. wait. Women and children first.

602
01:05:30.439 --> 01:05:33.839
Further in. everyone!

603
01:05:35.279 --> 01:05:38.679
-Get down! Come on.
-Further in!

604
01:05:39.799 --> 01:05:42.159
There are people waiting to get in!

605
01:05:42.239 --> 01:05:46.599
-Keep calm and go further in.
-Come on.

606
01:06:15.079 --> 01:06:17.479
Borghild! Borghild. Come.

607
01:06:31.639 --> 01:06:36.139
Further in! Spread out!
You have to spread out!

608
01:06:38.799 --> 01:06:40.439
Spread out!

609
01:06:40.599 --> 01:06:43.879
-Further in! Spread out!
-Further in.

610
01:06:43.959 --> 01:06:47.639
Colonel!
All lines of communication are broken.

611
01:07:40.319 --> 01:07:44.359
We have to get out!
Yes! We have to surrender!

612
01:07:44.439 --> 01:07:48.279
We can't just sit here and wait to die!

613
01:07:50.719 --> 01:07:54.079
-You can't go out.
-We have to! We're trapped!

614
01:07:54.599 --> 01:07:56.879
-Be quiet.
-They could be here any minute!

615
01:07:56.959 --> 01:07:59.079
You're scaring the others.

616
01:07:59.159 --> 01:08:02.159
-We have to surrender!
-Get it together!

617
01:08:02.239 --> 01:08:04.119
Egil? Do you have a light?

618
01:08:05.719 --> 01:08:08.239
-Huh?
-Do you have a light?

619
01:08:11.399 --> 01:08:13.959
-Yes?
-Yes.

620
01:08:31.719 --> 01:08:33.159
Look at me.

621
01:08:54.799 --> 01:08:57.799
-Does it hurt?
-Huh?

622
01:08:58.959 --> 01:09:02.959
Oh. No. it's fine. I just ...

623
01:09:04.959 --> 01:09:06.759
I just ...?

624
01:09:09.999 --> 01:09:12.199
I don't understand what's happening.

625
01:09:15.479 --> 01:09:17.839
That's alright.

626
01:09:20.319 --> 01:09:22.999
No one here understands what's happening.

627
01:11:58.119 --> 01:12:02.619
Reportedly. over five hundred bombs
were dropped on Oscarsborg.

628
01:12:04.159 --> 01:12:06.079
Where civilians were also present.

629
01:12:06.159 --> 01:12:10.079
They were trapped
in the tunnels with you. Eriksen?

630
01:12:10.159 --> 01:12:12.639
-Yes.
-Eriksen.

631
01:12:13.879 --> 01:12:18.359
Your daughter was also present
on the day in question?

632
01:12:25.639 --> 01:12:27.359
Was she present?

633
01:12:28.439 --> 01:12:30.279
Yes.

634
01:12:32.199 --> 01:12:34.479
Her being there ...

635
01:12:34.639 --> 01:12:39.139
Did that affect your judgment?
With regard to the decisions you made.

636
01:12:39.479 --> 01:12:42.479
which led to the surrender of the fort?

637
01:13:23.599 --> 01:13:25.599
No direct hits.

638
01:13:27.159 --> 01:13:28.679
No.

639
01:13:29.599 --> 01:13:31.479
Gather the troops.

640
01:13:31.639 --> 01:13:34.679
We are to hold the
fort as long as possible.

641
01:13:36.039 --> 01:13:37.599
Colonel.

642
01:13:50.959 --> 01:13:55.119
-Readying the guns will take a long time.
-No.

643
01:13:55.199 --> 01:13:59.119
Just get off the sand and dirt.
and they'll work.

644
01:13:59.199 --> 01:14:03.699
The men are spread out over the islands.
Morale is not at a high point right now.

645
01:14:06.239 --> 01:14:09.679
-Have a look at cannon one.
-Roger that.

646
01:14:52.159 --> 01:14:54.959
Are you alright? Are you alright?

647
01:14:57.239 --> 01:14:59.279
Where is the fire coming from?

648
01:15:01.159 --> 01:15:04.679
-Where is the fire coming from?
-There are new war ships ...

649
01:15:06.759 --> 01:15:08.119
Torpedo battery.

650
01:15:09.199 --> 01:15:10.719
Torpedo battery!

651
01:15:11.479 --> 01:15:13.239
The lines are down.

652
01:15:16.479 --> 01:15:19.359
Eriksen. Are you alright?

653
01:15:19.439 --> 01:15:21.119
Eriksen.

654
01:15:25.479 --> 01:15:29.979
The ship firing on the fort had
positioned itself far out in the fjord

655
01:15:31.199 --> 01:15:35.699
and directed all its firepower towards you.
That ship was Lützow.

656
01:15:36.119 --> 01:15:40.279
one of the ships which retreated
after Blücher was sunk.

657
01:15:40.359 --> 01:15:43.119
-Or got away.
-Eriksen.

658
01:15:43.199 --> 01:15:46.119
Did you return fire on Lützow?

659
01:15:48.959 --> 01:15:50.879
We were unable to.

660
01:15:52.239 --> 01:15:53.759
Why was that?

661
01:15:55.959 --> 01:15:58.439
We were unable to.

662
01:16:03.999 --> 01:16:08.119
In your opinion. what was the reason
you had to surrender the fort?

663
01:16:11.799 --> 01:16:13.919
-Anderssen!
-Yes.

664
01:16:14.919 --> 01:16:16.799
What's the situation here?

665
01:16:17.919 --> 01:16:19.359
No wounded.

666
01:16:19.439 --> 01:16:21.959
-Is the battery intact?
-Yes. yes.

667
01:16:22.039 --> 01:16:26.539
-What about Kopås?
-We don't know. The lines are down.

668
01:16:29.439 --> 01:16:31.319
Fetch a signal lamp.

669
01:16:32.439 --> 01:16:36.719
There's a new ship in the fjord.
We have to prepare for battle.

670
01:16:36.799 --> 01:16:40.959
The torpedo battery is intact.
We need the main battery operational.

671
01:16:41.039 --> 01:16:42.719
Colonel.

672
01:16:59.719 --> 01:17:02.879
The bombers could return at any time.

673
01:17:02.959 --> 01:17:05.959
We don't know
if we can fix the main battery.

674
01:17:05.999 --> 01:17:08.919
-Most of the men have been up all night.
-It's Kopås.

675
01:17:08.959 --> 01:17:11.199
Good. Are they ready for battle?

676
01:17:32.999 --> 01:17:36.759
Kopås signals:
one big warship at 8.000 metres.

677
01:17:36.839 --> 01:17:39.599
To smaller vessels bearing north.

678
01:17:41.799 --> 01:17:43.959
Kopås are ready to fire.

679
01:17:44.319 --> 01:17:47.679
Jesus. You can't let them fire now.

680
01:17:47.759 --> 01:17:52.159
If they concentrate their fire at Kopås.
everyone there will be blown to hell!

681
01:17:52.239 --> 01:17:54.799
The island will be a pile of rubble.

682
01:17:54.879 --> 01:17:58.359
You're the commanding officer.
You have to stop this madness!

683
01:18:01.799 --> 01:18:04.799
Tell Kopås
to hold their fire and wait for us.

684
01:18:05.879 --> 01:18:10.379
Send the following message:
"Hold your fire. Await further orders."

685
01:18:11.039 --> 01:18:14.039
I repeat.
"Hold your fire. Await further orders."

686
01:18:14.119 --> 01:18:18.399
We have to get the main battery
operational. so we can fire from both sides.

687
01:18:20.679 --> 01:18:22.439
Should we keep fighting?

688
01:18:22.599 --> 01:18:25.679
Our orders are
to hold the fort as long as possible.

689
01:18:25.759 --> 01:18:29.599
-Kopås have received the message.
-You should call a council of war.

690
01:18:29.679 --> 01:18:32.279
See what the officers think.

691
01:18:32.359 --> 01:18:36.279
Most of their families are here. since you
didn't want to evacuate them.

692
01:18:42.959 --> 01:18:45.119
Take cover! Run!

693
01:18:49.239 --> 01:18:51.439
Colonel! In here.

694
01:18:56.239 --> 01:18:58.319
The bombardment is constant!

695
01:18:59.479 --> 01:19:03.639
-It's over!
-The roof is about to collapse.

696
01:19:03.719 --> 01:19:06.159
There's no other alternative. Birger.

697
01:19:06.239 --> 01:19:08.079
Surrender!

698
01:19:22.479 --> 01:19:26.399
So you messaged Kopås.
"Hold fire and await further orders"?

699
01:19:27.719 --> 01:19:29.959
Yes ...

700
01:19:29.999 --> 01:19:31.799
But that was the last we heard.

701
01:19:31.879 --> 01:19:34.759
How did you choose to interpret that?

702
01:19:37.319 --> 01:19:39.079
That the fort had surrendered.

703
01:19:39.159 --> 01:19:41.759
-We hadn't.
-Alright. Eriksen.

704
01:19:42.919 --> 01:19:47.419
So what. then. was the reason
you had to surrender. in your view?

705
01:20:00.199 --> 01:20:01.919
What's going on up there?

706
01:20:05.119 --> 01:20:08.759
Kopås and the Drøbak side have been taken.

707
01:20:10.999 --> 01:20:12.479
The Germans ...

708
01:20:13.359 --> 01:20:16.639
... want to negotiate a surrender.

709
01:20:18.079 --> 01:20:19.599
Otherwise ...

710
01:20:21.399 --> 01:20:24.319
Otherwise they will start bombing ...

711
01:20:24.399 --> 01:20:25.839
Drøbak ...

712
01:20:27.119 --> 01:20:28.479
... and Oslo.

713
01:20:33.359 --> 01:20:35.159
What's our reply?

714
01:21:03.679 --> 01:21:07.359
Send message: "We are ready to negotiate."

715
01:21:35.199 --> 01:21:39.699
German forces took the Kopås battery
without firing a single shot.

716
01:21:42.719 --> 01:21:46.399
But I never meant for you not to resist.

717
01:21:46.479 --> 01:21:50.979
How many people died
at Oscarsborg. Eriksen?

718
01:21:53.759 --> 01:21:56.039
None.

719
01:21:56.119 --> 01:21:59.599
Your orders were
to hold the fort as long as possible.

720
01:21:59.679 --> 01:22:02.639
You were
the commanding officer of Oscarsborg?

721
01:22:02.719 --> 01:22:07.219
What was it. Eriksen?
What was the reason you had to surrender?

722
01:22:10.999 --> 01:22:13.239
That Kopås was taken.

723
01:22:13.319 --> 01:22:15.079
That's incorrect.

724
01:22:18.639 --> 01:22:20.959
The Kopås guns could've been turned on us.

725
01:22:20.999 --> 01:22:23.759
-We had no choice.
-That's not true.

726
01:22:23.839 --> 01:22:28.339
The order to hold fire
was the reason we surrendered.

727
01:22:28.959 --> 01:22:31.719
The reason we had to abandon Kopås.

728
01:22:31.799 --> 01:22:36.299
-Eriksen had decided to give up the fort.
-That was not the meaning of the order.

729
01:22:37.959 --> 01:22:42.459
When the lines are down. the battery chief
must make his own decision.

730
01:22:56.879 --> 01:23:01.379
I think the Commission
has heard what it needs to today.

731
01:23:02.959 --> 01:23:06.719
We will return with our final conclusion.

732
01:23:06.799 --> 01:23:09.119
We would like to thank the gentlemen ...

733
01:23:09.199 --> 01:23:13.199
Has the Commission
asked itself the question ...

734
01:23:13.279 --> 01:23:17.779
what would have happened
if we had been prepared that night?

735
01:23:21.839 --> 01:23:23.799
What do you mean. Eriksen?

736
01:23:23.879 --> 01:23:28.379
If the coastal forts were fully mobilised
and armed. so no ships could have passed.

737
01:23:29.999 --> 01:23:34.359
if runways had been barricaded.
preventing planes from landing ...

738
01:23:38.479 --> 01:23:42.979
... the German assault would have failed
Or been prevented altogether!

739
01:23:47.999 --> 01:23:52.499
I assume it is the government
which has appointed this Commission.

740
01:23:55.799 --> 01:24:00.299
If you are asking who is responsible
for the surrender of Oscarsborg.

741
01:24:00.839 --> 01:24:05.339
It is the 1940 government who
ought to be cross-examined here today!

742
01:24:07.799 --> 01:24:11.999
They should have to answer
why the military was not prioritised.

743
01:24:12.079 --> 01:24:15.079
In spite of the state of the world
and countless warnings!

744
01:24:15.159 --> 01:24:18.919
I've written multiple requests
for reinforcements of Oscarsborg.

745
01:24:18.959 --> 01:24:23.359
Every request was denied!

746
01:24:29.759 --> 01:24:34.259
To divert attention from the failed
defensive policies and those who didn't act.

747
01:24:36.079 --> 01:24:38.919
you come after the officers ...

748
01:24:39.759 --> 01:24:42.039
... who actually did something.

749
01:24:43.799 --> 01:24:45.719
We did our best.

750
01:27:15.959 --> 01:27:20.459
It is this Commission's firm conviction that
Enger and Sødem's statements are correct.

751
01:27:23.479 --> 01:27:27.979
Eriksen's command to hold fire led
to the surrender of Kopås to the enemy.

752
01:27:31.439 --> 01:27:35.939
Eriksen's account
can therefore not be accurate.

753
01:27:47.399 --> 01:27:51.899
The Investigative Commission of 1946
examined the battle of Oscarsborg.

754
01:27:52.639 --> 01:27:57.139
Their report found not a single word
of praise for Eriksen's actions.

755
01:29:09.399 --> 01:29:12.839
Eriksen's order to open fire is considered

756
01:29:12.919 --> 01:29:16.439
the most important single act
in Norway during WWII.

757
01:29:19.199 --> 01:29:23.699
The delay of the invasion allowed
the King and the Government to evacuate.

758
01:29:28.999 --> 01:29:33.499
Birger Eriksen remained in Drøbak
with his wife and his daughter Borghild

759
01:29:34.119 --> 01:29:37.399
until his death in 1958.

760
01:29:51.999 --> 01:29:55.999
Subtitles: Johannes E. Refsdal
Nortext
